past the checkpoints.

05:28.562 --> 05:32.064
Abraham, no one is conducting
business over the holiday.

05:34.400 --> 05:36.802
Which leaves us
with no competition.

05:36.804 --> 05:39.037
See, all the fighting
has stopped for the winter,

05:39.039 --> 05:42.741
so Howe's entire army
is bunkered down in the city.

05:42.743 --> 05:44.476
Just think of the demand
that this creates.

05:44.478 --> 05:47.346
Now is the time to
renegotiate our contract.

05:47.348 --> 05:51.550
Alas, we've struck
a gentlemen's deal with Cook.

05:51.552 --> 05:53.952
<i>You want me</i>
<i>to give you his letter</i>

05:53.954 --> 05:56.355
so you can sell
to somebody else?

05:56.357 --> 05:58.023
<i>The army has needs.</i>

05:58.025 --> 06:00.525
The city's population
will have tripled.

06:02.829 --> 06:05.697
Why are you so anxious
to go to New York?

06:07.834 --> 06:10.769
Don't you want to celebrate
Christmas with your family,

06:10.771 --> 06:12.070
with your wife and child?

06:12.072 --> 06:15.941
Of course I do,
but, uh...

06:15.943 --> 06:17.776
I must provide
for them first.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.678
Well, if it's
a question of a loan...

06:19.680 --> 06:21.913
- No.
- <i>...to get you</i>
<i> through the winter.</i>

06:21.915 --> 06:23.615
- I don't want--
- <i>Mary doesn't have to know.</i>

06:23.617 --> 06:25.784
I want nothing from you.

06:29.622 --> 06:31.723
I had noticed
you'd been avoiding me

06:31.725 --> 06:34.459
since the fortification
of the barracks.

06:34.461 --> 06:36.595
"The fortification."

06:37.730 --> 06:39.965
Is that truly
what you're calling it?

06:39.967 --> 06:42.934
I call it my duty
and I would do it again.

06:42.936 --> 06:45.971
Well, good.
You still have your wife's
gravestone to tear out.

06:55.615 --> 06:59.418
She would know
you didn't mean that.

06:59.420 --> 07:02.754
Just the same as you
saying you want nothing
from me is untrue.

07:04.056 --> 07:08.794
You want my pass to the city
and I do not grant it

07:08.796 --> 07:12.731
<i>because I know that you</i>
<i>running from your home,</i>

07:12.733 --> 07:16.168
from our family,
will not bring you peace.

07:20.673 --> 07:23.608
I will be
celebrating Christmas
at my house this year,

07:23.610 --> 07:26.545
with my family.

07:26.547 --> 07:28.180
Don't expect us.

08:22.668 --> 08:25.570
<i>( soldier shouting orders )</i>

08:27.840 --> 08:30.575
Anna:
<i>Please understand,</i>
<i>I'm not here to dispute</i>

08:30.577 --> 08:33.544
<i>the attainder</i>
<i>against my husband</i>
<i>or his estate.</i>

08:33.547 --> 08:36.014
It is the military
provision within it,

08:36.015 --> 08:37.816
this Dunmore Proclamation,

08:37.818 --> 08:40.184
that forms the basis
of my complaint.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.220
Please do tell us

08:42.222 --> 08:44.656
what fault you find
with Lord Dunmore.

08:45.558 --> 08:48.093
Not with
the man himself.

08:49.829 --> 08:52.163
It's just--

08:52.165 --> 08:54.666
it's cruel,

08:54.668 --> 08:58.270
this business
of freeing slaves
of suspected Patriots.

08:58.272 --> 09:00.839
I am sincerely sorry

09:00.841 --> 09:02.941
that you're being punished
for your husband's actions,

09:02.943 --> 09:06.878
but he is a confirmed
insurrectionist, madam,
not a suspected one.

09:08.581 --> 09:11.750
These poor souls
have never had to provide
for themselves.

09:11.752 --> 09:14.586
And now you give them
a mere seven days

09:14.588 --> 09:16.221
to prepare for a life
they have never known.

09:16.223 --> 09:19.224
Were their forefathers
given a chance to prepare

09:19.226 --> 09:21.593
when they were plucked
from the Dark Continent

09:21.595 --> 09:23.328
and introduced
to these shores?

09:24.864 --> 09:28.867
Sir, I have known
some of them all
my life and--

09:28.869 --> 09:30.735
Slavery is a sin,

09:30.737 --> 09:33.805
<i>which is why it</i>
<i>has just been legally</i>
<i>abolished in England</i>

09:33.807 --> 09:36.341
and, I expect,
soon throughout
the Crown Colonies.

09:36.343 --> 09:40.178
<i>The Dunmore Proclamation</i>
<i>will be upheld.</i>

09:41.781 --> 09:44.349
The able men
will go to New York
and join the war effort,

09:44.351 --> 09:46.952
<i>and as for the women,</i>
<i>I've already arranged</i>

09:46.954 --> 09:49.287
a perfect opportunity
for your housemaid.

09:49.289 --> 09:50.789
It's, uh--

09:50.791 --> 09:54.192
uh, Abigail, is it?

09:55.895 --> 09:59.030
All right.

10:08.374 --> 10:10.075
It was your father's.

10:13.079 --> 10:15.914
He'd have been so proud
that you can read.

10:15.916 --> 10:18.249
- It's mine to keep?
- ( laughs )

