10:19.786 --> 10:22.287
Jordan: <i>Hey.</i>

10:22.289 --> 10:24.055
You hungry, big man?

10:24.057 --> 10:26.791
Eh? You smell
that balangu?

10:26.793 --> 10:30.061
You smell
that balangu, huh?

10:30.063 --> 10:32.263
You best hurry before
the whole thing gone.

10:32.265 --> 10:34.032
Go on.

10:36.002 --> 10:38.903
How often must I tell you
not to push into my place?

10:38.905 --> 10:43.174
You only got about seven days
to see what you're missing.

10:43.176 --> 10:46.311
Once New Year come,
I get them papers, I gone.

10:46.313 --> 10:48.913
Then I wish you
safe passage.

10:50.816 --> 10:53.151
Maybe you're not ready
to walk free in this world.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.654
( scoffs )
'Cause I won't
lay down with you?

10:55.656 --> 10:59.057
That's a different
kind of walk.

10:59.059 --> 11:02.293
City walk.
Eyes forward,
not to the ground.

11:02.295 --> 11:05.196
Oh, you know that walk?

11:05.198 --> 11:07.732
I was born free.

11:07.734 --> 11:10.435
Then walk free
with one of your gals.

11:12.371 --> 11:14.673
They ain't important.

11:15.741 --> 11:17.442
Not like you.

11:17.444 --> 11:20.178
Abigail:
<i>Why am I so important</i>
<i>all of a sudden?</i>

11:20.180 --> 11:23.114
Well, you can read,
can't you?

11:24.917 --> 11:27.118
Jordan:
<i>Don't be afraid, Abby.</i>

11:27.120 --> 11:29.821
I know your secret
since way back.

11:33.392 --> 11:37.862
Look, if you treat me right,
maybe I'll stick with ya.

11:38.931 --> 11:41.700
I'll protect
you and your boy.

11:41.702 --> 11:43.468
You gonna need
a strong man.

11:43.470 --> 11:45.737
My son is all I need.

11:50.009 --> 11:52.444
You think
you better than me?

11:52.446 --> 11:56.214
- I never said--
- Gals like you,
always cold.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.982
But watch.

11:57.984 --> 12:01.252
You gon' end
with nothing.

12:10.262 --> 12:11.996
Soldier: <i>Major Rogers</i>
<i>has come to wish you</i>

12:11.998 --> 12:13.431
<i>a happy</i>
<i>Christmastide, sir.</i>

12:13.433 --> 12:16.267
Lieutenant-Colonel
Commandant is his title.

12:16.269 --> 12:18.036
He hasn't been Major Rogers

12:18.038 --> 12:20.405
since he fought the French
and their native allies.

12:20.407 --> 12:22.774
Ah, so this is
where your commander

12:22.776 --> 12:24.909
keeps all
his favorite boys.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.277
<i>Not bad, Johnny.</i>

12:26.279 --> 12:28.179
Did you follow me here?

12:28.181 --> 12:31.216
It wasn't hard to track ya.
Us Rangers always get our man.

12:31.218 --> 12:34.753
Oh, so you found
that dragoon you've been
hunting at long last?

12:34.755 --> 12:37.122
<i>Oh, no, I recall.</i>

12:37.124 --> 12:39.290
You came back
from Long Island
empty-handed.

12:39.292 --> 12:42.260
And the bird sings to me
that you came back
from New Jersey

12:42.262 --> 12:45.163
<i>with a captured</i>
<i>general in tow.</i>

12:45.165 --> 12:48.133
I should wish
to talk with your prize.

12:48.135 --> 12:49.834
Where is he?

12:53.439 --> 12:57.041
The birds tell me
your Rangers have been
foraging for purpose,

12:57.043 --> 13:01.212
offering to take
any task for any sum.

13:02.214 --> 13:04.082
For the Crown.

13:04.084 --> 13:07.051
Just because you lot
plan to slumber all winter

13:07.053 --> 13:08.953
doesn't mean Georgie does.

13:08.955 --> 13:10.789
Have you intelligence
to share?

13:10.791 --> 13:13.191
I have experience.

13:13.193 --> 13:15.527
Georgie fought
alongside me in the wild,

13:15.529 --> 13:19.531
not in the dainty fields
of Europe where rules matter.

13:19.533 --> 13:23.234
Still, when the bounties
of his men expire next week,

13:23.236 --> 13:26.471
he shall be short
precisely one army,

13:26.473 --> 13:31.476
and General Howe
will no longer have use
for the hounds of war.

13:35.581 --> 13:38.349
Tell me, Robert,
what do you intend to do

13:38.351 --> 13:40.919
when this war
is officially over?

13:40.921 --> 13:43.488
Return to settle
your estate?

13:43.490 --> 13:45.290
Your debts?

13:48.394 --> 13:52.030
Apologies, sir.
Your presence is
requested by General--

13:56.235 --> 14:00.004
Oh, I aim to settle
all accounts, boy.

14:02.408 --> 14:06.477
Frederick, please show
my guest out.

14:06.479 --> 14:07.979
Frederick:
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

14:07.981 --> 14:11.015
Happy New Year, Major.

14:13.118 --> 14:14.919
To peace!

14:19.525 --> 14:21.459
Major:
<i>Tallmadge,</i>
<i>on your feet.</i>

14:21.461 --> 14:22.861
Sir.

14:22.863 --> 14:24.529
Muster out and collect
your supplies.

14:24.531 --> 14:27.098
Every man gets three
days' cooked rations,

14:27.100 --> 14:29.434
40 rounds of ammunition,
fresh flints, and a blanket.

14:29.436 --> 14:32.403
- For what, sir?
- Secret mission, they say.

14:32.405 --> 14:35.073
Password challenge
is "victory."

14:35.075 --> 14:37.242
And the answer, sir?

14:37.244 --> 14:39.077
"Or death."

14:53.926 --> 14:57.195
- Caleb!
- What?

14:57.197 --> 14:59.030
You know what this
is all about?

14:59.032 --> 15:02.166
Me? No.
Thought you would.

15:02.168 --> 15:05.503
All they told me
is we're crossing
the Delaware.

15:05.505 --> 15:08.139
Great.

15:08.141 --> 15:10.208
They told us
just to follow you.

15:10.210 --> 15:13.044
<i>Huh?</i>

15:15.614 --> 15:18.983
Well, you're the whaler.

15:18.985 --> 15:22.186
As long as we're
crossing, he's captain.

15:22.188 --> 15:23.554
That's me.

15:23.556 --> 15:28.626
So, you, you, and you
grab the push-poles.

15:28.628 --> 15:31.229
Right, push off!

15:33.632 --> 15:35.967
( boat creaking )

15:43.509 --> 15:46.644
Caleb:
I mean, you ask me, this is
just a glorified scout.

15:46.646 --> 15:49.681
Secret password,
"Victory or death."

15:49.683 --> 15:52.016
No, Washington's
just trying to make us

15:52.018 --> 15:54.285
feel like we're
still in the fight.

15:54.287 --> 15:56.688
Caleb, look.

16:03.495 --> 16:05.296
Jesus.

16:05.298 --> 16:08.299
This is no scout.

16:30.723 --> 16:32.724
I'm sorry.

16:32.726 --> 16:34.292
I was being silly.

16:34.294 --> 16:37.128
No.

16:37.130 --> 16:38.997
Do you like it?

16:38.999 --> 16:42.000
It's beautiful.

16:42.002 --> 16:43.701
It's yours.

16:43.703 --> 16:47.472
- I insist.
- ( laughs ) I couldn't--

16:47.474 --> 16:51.175
Please, take it.

16:56.648 --> 17:00.051
I know how impossible
this all must be for you.

17:00.053 --> 17:03.087
I want you to know
that I am here

17:03.089 --> 17:05.256
and I will continue
working for you in
this difficult time...

17:05.258 --> 17:06.790
- Abigail...
- ...for whatever
you can pay.

17:06.792 --> 17:09.127
we will survive this.

17:10.396 --> 17:12.096
Even when I'm free,
we shall still be friends.

17:12.098 --> 17:13.598
You're not going
to be free.

17:15.401 --> 17:18.336
Major Hewlett is hell-bent
on making a gift of you

17:18.338 --> 17:20.438
to a British officer
in New York.

17:22.374 --> 17:26.044
